Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: As this series barrels toward its conclusion, Naruto and the Shinobi Alliance continue their battle against Obito.
Title: NARUTO, VOL. 68
Author: Masashi Kishimoto

Description: The students of class of 3–E have only one assignment: kill the teacher! Of course, when that teacher is also a supremely powerful being, it is easier said than done.
Title: ASSASSINATION CLASSROOM, VOL. 1
Author: Yusei Matsui

Description: Kirito has escaped from the virtual reality world of Sword Art Online, but now, he must go inside another game to try and save the woman he loves.
Title: SWORD ART ONLINE: FAIRY DANCE, VOL. 2
Author: Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki
Contributor: by Reki Kawahara and Tsubasa Haduki

Description: Follow the virtual (and musical) adventures of Hatsune Miku and her friends in this collected edition of stories, in black and white and color.
Title: UNOFFICIAL HATSUNE MIX
Author: KEI

Description: The origins of the Survey Corps leaders Levi and Erwin are told in this spin–off series.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: NO REGRETS, VOL. 1
Author: Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama
Contributor: by Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama

Description: The origins of the Survey Corps leaders Levi and Erwin are told in this spinoff series.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: NO REGRETS, VOL. 2
Author: Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama
Contributor: by Gun Snark, Hikaru Suruga and Hajime Isayama

Description: Mankind has gone into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans. In this volume, the Titans attack and one of them goes rogue.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 2
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Kraft Lawrence, a young merchant finds himself with a companion: Holo, the Wolf–God of the harvest.
Title: SPICE AND WOLF, VOL. 10
Author: Isuna Hasekura and Keito Koume
Contributor: by Isuna Hasekura and Keito Koume

Description: This series adapts the plot from the role–playing video game, where a young boy must save a magical kingdom with his allies Donald Duck and Goofy.
Title: KINGDOM HEARTS II, VOL. 3
Author: Shiro Amano
